last_episode_to_air.name: Come Along With Me
last_episode_to_air.overview: In the distant future, many years after the outcome of the Gum War, two friends named Beth and Shermy recover a rusty old mechanical arm that once belonged to Finn after it is dropped by a Prize Ball Guardian.

name: Adventure Time
overview: Hook up with Finn and Jake as they travel the Land of Ooo searching for adventure. But remember, adventure isn’t always easy. Sometimes you’ve got to battle fire gnomes that torture old ladies, save a smelly hot dog princess from the Ice King, and thaw out a bunch of frozen businessmen. What the cabbage?!

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Soon after airing, the show began to receive critical acclaim as well as a large fan following. In 2010, the Adventure Time episode "My Two Favorite People" was even nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Short-format Animated Program, although the series did not win.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In 2011, Adventure Time was nominated for an Annie Award, and the episode "It Came from the Nightosphere" was nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Short-format Animated Program.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: The season was met with largely positive critical reception. In addition, several episodes and writers were nominated for awards; the episode "Thank You" was nominated for an Annie Award as well as an award at the Sundance Film Festival. "Too Young" was nominated for an Emmy Award. Storyboard artist Rebecca Sugar was also nominated for an Annie Award.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The season was met with largely positive critical reception. In addition, several episodes were nominated for awards; The episodes "Princess Cookie", "The Hard Easy", "Lady & Peebles", and "Goliad" were all nominated for Annie Awards. The episode "Card Wars", however, won a Golden Reel Awards.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: The season has been met with largely positive critical reception. In June 2013, the series was nominated for "Best Animated Series" at the 2013 Critics' Choice Television Awards. At the 65th Primetime Emmy Awards, "Simon & Marcy", was nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Short-format Animation, and former character designer Andy Ristaino won an Emmy for "Outstanding Individual Achievement In Animation" for his character designs in the episode "Puhoy".

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: The season follows the adventures of Finn the Human, a human boy, and his best friend Jake, a dog with magical powers to change shape, grow, and shrink at will. Finn and Jake live in the post-apocalyptic Land of Ooo. Along the way, they interact with the other main characters of the show: Princess Bubblegum, The Ice King, and Marceline the Vampire Queen. Common storylines revolve around Finn and Jake discovering strange creatures, dealing with the antagonistic but misunderstood Ice King, and battling monsters in order to help others.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: Main story arcs for this season include Bubblegum adjusting to life in exile and eventually reclaiming the Candy Kingdom crown, and Marceline coming to terms with her vampiric nature.

seasons.name: Season 10
seasons.overview: The tenth and final season of Adventure Time.

episodes.name: Sky Witch

episodes.name: Frost & Fire

episodes.name: Love Games
episodes.overview: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sis. Finn steps in to save the day, but first they will need to win a series of Love Games to prove to Slime Princess's dad that they are really in love. This is definitely not what Finn signed up for!

episodes.name: Dungeon Train
episodes.overview: All aboard! Finn and Jake discover a train where every car is a dungeon filled with a new foe for Finn to fight. Jake quickly gets bored and wants to leave, but Finn is having the best time and doesn't want to leave... ever!

episodes.name: Box Prince

episodes.name: Red Starved

If Marceline doesn't feed, like ASAP, she will turn into a vampiric beast and suck out all of Jake's blood! So, Finn heads off to explore the cave and find something red to satiate her until they can be rescued. But time is running out!

episodes.name: We Fixed a Truck
episodes.overview: Finn finds an old truck, and Jake calls Banana Man to help with the repairs. But when BMO stays up all night working on the truck, he hears on a spooky radio talk show that Princess Bubblegum is a reptilian replicant. Is it just another one of Starchy's crazy conspiracy theories, or a fact?

episodes.name: Play Date
episodes.overview: Sick and tired of babysitting Ice King while the Ice Kingdom is being rebuilt, Finn and Jake call up an old friend to hang out with their annoying houseguest: Abracadaniel.

episodes.name: The Pit
episodes.overview: Finn needs Lady Rainicorn's help to rescue Jake when he is kidnapped by Kee-Oth the Blood Demon.

episodes.name: James
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, and Princess Bubblegum are attacked by nasty goo monsters in the Desert of Wonders.

episodes.name: Root Beer Guy
episodes.overview: Root Beer Guy works a boring job during the day and tries to write mystery stories at night. But his life is about to change when he witnesses Finn and Jake kidnapping Princess Bubblegum! There's only one problem: no one believes Root Beer Guy...

episodes.name: Apple Wedding
episodes.overview: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig are celebrating the wedding of the year.

episodes.name: Blade of Grass
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake decide it's time for Finn to get a new sword. Finn reluctantly buys a grass sword from a mysterious old man, but the sword turns out to be cursed! And unfortunately for our hero, all sales are final.

episodes.name: Rattleballs
episodes.overview: Finn practices his sword fighting skills at the candy junkyard, where he meets an old gumball robot named Rattleballs. To Finn's shock, he finds out he's not the master swordsman he thinks he is. What the what?! Finn begs Rattleballs to train him, but he soon discovers his mentor's deep, dark secret... a secret that will ultimately test Finn's loyalty to Princess Bubblegum.

episodes.name: The Red Throne
episodes.overview: When Flame King breaks out of his prison and takes over the Flame Kingdom again, Flame Princess turns to the one person she believes she can trust... Finn! But will Finn be able to put his feelings for Flame Princess aside long enough to help her reclaim her throne?

episodes.name: Betty
episodes.overview: After a magic spell backfires, the Ice King reverts back to Simon, and seeks help from Finn, Jake, and Marceline in order to get Betty, his former fiancée, back.

episodes.name: Bad Timing
episodes.overview: Love is in the air when Lumpy Space Princess reconnects with an old classmate, but will her jealousy get in the way of finding true love?

episodes.name: Lemonhope (1)
episodes.overview: Tired of all of Princess Bubblegum's talk about "responsibility," Lemonhope yearns for true freedom. So he sets off on the greatest adventure of his lemony life.

episodes.name: Lemonhope (2)
episodes.overview: Though Lemonhope finds refuge from the desert with monster hunter Phlannel Boxingday, he might not be able to escape the ghosts of his past.

episodes.name: Billy's Bucket List
episodes.overview: Finn finds the hero Billy's bucket list and decides to complete the unfinished items as a final tribute.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: The season has been met with largely positive critical reception. In June 2013, the series was nominated for "Best Animated Series" at the 2013 Critics' Choice Television Awards. At the 65th Primetime Emmy Awards, "Simon & Marcy", was nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Short-format Animation, and former character designer Andy Ristaino won an Emmy for "Outstanding Individual Achievement In Animation" for his character designs in the episode "Puhoy".

episodes.name: Wake Up
episodes.overview: In order to find Finn's father, Finn and Jake must commit a cosmic crime...unless the Lich beats them to it.

episodes.name: Escape from the Citadel
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake follow the Lich to the Citadel, where Finn meets his long lost dad. But just how far does the apple fall from the tree?

episodes.name: James II
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake discover that Clone James has been faking his own death to collect medals. Now there are 25 Jameses running amok!

episodes.name: The Tower
episodes.overview: Finn doesn't like any of the new arms the princesses give him, so he builds a tower into space to find his dad and get his old arm back. But are his hopes up a little too high?

episodes.name: Sad Face
episodes.overview: Once a month, while Jake's asleep, his tail stretches out of the tree house to go work as a clown in a traveling bug circus.

episodes.name: Breezy
episodes.overview: With a friendly bee named "Breezy" as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

episodes.name: Food Chain
episodes.overview: On a field trip to the Candy Kingdom Museum of Natural History, Finn and Jake learn about the food chain by becoming the food chain!

episodes.name: Furniture & Meat
episodes.overview: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

episodes.name: The Prince Who Wanted Everything
episodes.overview: The beautiful and sensitive Lumpy Space Prince flees his cruel parents to start a new life.

episodes.name: Something Big
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum must rally her forces when the Candy Kingdom is rocked by a massive assault.

episodes.name: Little Brother
episodes.overview: Shelby the worm discovers that he has a little brother who is bound for adventure in the nooks of Marceline's tree house.

episodes.name: Ocarina
episodes.overview: Fed up with Jake's antics, his son Kim Kil Whan takes action.

episodes.name: Thanks for the Crabapples, Giuseppe!
episodes.overview: Ice King and a band of misfit wizards go on a mystical road trip.

episodes.name: Princess Day
episodes.overview: It's Princess Day in Ooo! You know what that means? Yep, LSP and Marceline team up to prank Breakfast Princess!

episodes.name: Nemesis
episodes.overview: A shadowy figure named Peace Master targets the Candy Kingdom elite.

episodes.name: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

episodes.name: Ghost Fly
episodes.overview: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful specter.

episodes.name: Everything's Jake
episodes.overview: Jake finds himself trapped in a world made of himself.

episodes.name: Is That You?
episodes.overview: Following an ally's memorial service, Jake begins acting strangely.

episodes.name: Jake the Brick
episodes.overview: Jake wants to fulfill a bizarre lifelong ambition.

episodes.name: Dentist
episodes.overview: When Finn's toothache gets too much to take, he has no choice but to go see dentist.

episodes.name: The Cooler
episodes.overview: When the Fire Kingdom is struck by a natural disaster, Flame Princess turns to an unlikely ally.

episodes.name: The Pajama War
episodes.overview: A Candy Kingdom slumber party devolves into panic when Finn and Princess Bubblegum vanish.

episodes.name: Evergreen
episodes.overview: In a distant age, the wizard Evergreen quests to save the world.

episodes.name: Astral Plane
episodes.overview: Finn's spirit is drawn into the astral plane by the power of the mysterious comet.

episodes.name: Gold Stars
episodes.overview: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig's child, Sweet P, runs into trouble on his first day of school.

episodes.name: The Visitor
episodes.overview: Finn meets a friendly civilization and a sees a mysterious crash site in a vision.

episodes.name: The Mountain
episodes.overview: Lemongrab and Finn go on an expedition through the Mountain of Matthew.

episodes.name: Dark Purple
episodes.overview: Susan Strong and her allies infiltrate the mysterious Super Porp factory.

episodes.name: The Diary
episodes.overview: Jake's son TV discovers a lost diary and sets out to solve a decades-old mystery.

episodes.name: Walnuts & Rain
episodes.overview: When Finn and Jake stumble into two different holes, they meet two different fates.

episodes.name: Friends Forever
episodes.overview: Ice King has a plan to form a perfect circle of confidants.

episodes.name: Jermaine
episodes.overview: After a chilling dream encounter, Finn & Jake are determined to reconnect with their reclusive brother.

episodes.name: Chips & Ice Cream
episodes.overview: BMO'S favorite artists find a new home in the treehouse.

episodes.name: Graybles 1000+
episodes.overview: Marooned on an alien world, Cuber must rely on his bag of Graybles to survive.

episodes.name: Hoots
episodes.overview: A charismatic stranger in Finn's dream leads Cosmic Owl to shirk his duties.

episodes.name: Water Park Prank
episodes.overview: After rescuing Princess Orangutan from Daddy-sad-heads, Finn and Jake head to a post-apocalyptic water park for a day of fun.

episodes.name: You Forgot Your Floaties
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake storm Magic Man's house to rescue his new apprentice.

episodes.name: Be Sweet
episodes.overview: A fed up Lumpy Space Princess leaves the woods for a glamorous career in babysitting.

episodes.name: Orgalorg
episodes.overview: After a walrus race accident, Gunther starts to experience strange visions.

episodes.name: On the Lam
episodes.overview: Finn's dad Martin the Human fights for freedom on a strange new planet!

episodes.name: Hot Diggity Doom
episodes.overview: It's election day in the Candy Kingdom but Princess Bubblegum's attention is diverted by a mysterious presence in the sky.

episodes.name: The Comet
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and Orgalorg converge with the comet and meet their destiny.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview: The season follows the adventures of Finn the Human, a human boy, and his best friend Jake, a dog with magical powers to change shape, grow, and shrink at will. Finn and Jake live in the post-apocalyptic Land of Ooo. Along the way, they interact with the other main characters of the show: Princess Bubblegum, The Ice King, and Marceline the Vampire Queen. Common storylines revolve around Finn and Jake discovering strange creatures, dealing with the antagonistic but misunderstood Ice King, and battling monsters in order to help others.

episodes.name: Bonnie and Neddy
episodes.overview: The greed of the King of Ooo leads to a crisis in the Candy Kingdom, and (ex-) Princess Bubblegum has to return briefly from exile to deal with it.

episodes.name: Varmints
episodes.overview: Bubblegum turns to Marceline's help when something threatens the citizens of her homestead.

episodes.name: Cherry Cream Soda
episodes.overview: The arrival of a visitor causes Cherry Cream Soda's life to fall flat.

episodes.name: Mama Said
episodes.overview: The loyalty of Finn and Jake comes into question when the King of Ooo orders them to intercept a flying mushroom.

episodes.name: Football
episodes.overview: BMO and Football decide upon a deal, but one of them cannot keep up their end of the bargain.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake hunt a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a favor.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
episodes.overview: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
episodes.overview: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
episodes.overview: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

episodes.name: Stakes Part 6: Take Her Back
episodes.overview: While Princess Bubblegum searches for a cure for Marceline, Finn and Jake take on one of the Vamps themselves.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 7: Checkmate
episodes.overview: On the eve of battle, Marceline's archenemy comes to her with a strange proposal.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 8: The Dark Cloud
episodes.overview: The final confrontation begins. Who will survive?

episodes.name: The More You Moe, The Moe You Know (1)
episodes.overview: On BMO's birthday, Moe comes to visit and give BMO a special birthday mission. But while BMO is away, Moe begins to overstay his welcome at the tree house.

episodes.name: The More You Moe, The Moe You Know (2)
episodes.overview: BMO continues its quest to adulthood. It'll discover that something went wrong in the factory where all the MOs where created.

episodes.name: Summer Showers
episodes.overview: Viola tries to get a part in LSP's play, but gets made into LSP's personal assistant instead.

episodes.name: Angel Face
episodes.overview: BMO convinces his friends to join him in a live action cowboy role-playing game.

episodes.name: President Porpoise Is Missing!
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake attempt to track down President Porpoise before Vice President Blowfish takes over.

episodes.name: Blank Eyed Girl
episodes.overview: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

episodes.name: Bad Jubies
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, LSP and BMO seek shelter as they contend with some deadly weather.

episodes.name: King's Ransom
episodes.overview: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

episodes.name: Scamps
episodes.overview: Finn takes a group of at-risk Candy Kingdom youth on a camping trip they’ll never forget.

episodes.name: Crossover
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake crossover into Farmworld Finn's dimension.

episodes.name: The Hall of Egress
episodes.overview: Trapped and alone, Finn must unravel the riddle of the weird cave with no exit.

episodes.name: Flute Spell
episodes.overview: Finn has secret meetings with a powerful wizard.

episodes.name: The Thin Yellow Line
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake infiltrate the Banana Guard ranks and stumble upon a conspiracy.

7.name: Season 7
7.overview: Main story arcs for this season include Bubblegum adjusting to life in exile and eventually reclaiming the Candy Kingdom crown, and Marceline coming to terms with her vampiric nature.

episodes.name: Broke His Crown
episodes.overview: When Ice King's magic crown goes haywire, Marceline and Princess Bubblegum resort to extreme measures to help him.

episodes.name: Don't Look
episodes.overview: Finn unearths a treasure with a terrible price at the top of Dead Mountain.

episodes.name: Beyond the Grotto
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake follow their Sea Lard into the pond in front of their home, and in doing so, are led to a strange new world.

episodes.name: Lady Rainicorn of the Crystal Dimension
episodes.overview: Jake's son finds a hidden box and draws attention from a Rainicorn.

episodes.name: I am a Sword
episodes.overview: When Finn begins having nightmares about his missing Finn Sword, he wonders if they are real.

episodes.name: Bun Bun
episodes.overview: Finn brings a special delivery for Cinnamon Bun to the Fire Kingdom but it may come with a dangerous cost.

episodes.name: Normal Man
episodes.overview: Normal Man asks for Finn and Jake's help to rescue his brother.

episodes.name: Elemental
episodes.overview: Ice King digs up an item buried underneath the Ice Kingdom.

episodes.name: Five Short Tables
episodes.overview: Fionna and Cake go on a cooking adventure to push Cake's art to an all-new level.

episodes.name: The Music Hole
episodes.overview: Finn hears a mysterious song while judging a Battle of the Bands.

episodes.name: Daddy-Daughter Card Wars
episodes.overview: Jake and his daughter Charlie fight to restore Jake's honor and win a super-secret underground Card Wars tourney.

episodes.name: Preboot
episodes.overview: While searching for old human artifacts, Jake, Finn, and Susan Strong meet Tiffany, who is employed by a mysterious Doctor Gross.

episodes.name: Reboot
episodes.overview: After Susan Strong's chip is activated, she goes rogue and attacks Finn.

episodes.name: Two Swords
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake puzzle over the nature of a mysterious newcomer.

episodes.name: Do No Harm
episodes.overview: Doctor Princess thrusts a great responsibility upon Finn. Jake goes adventuring with a new friend.

episodes.name: Wheels
episodes.overview: Kim Kil Whan is worried about his daughter's future and asks Jake for some parental advice.

episodes.name: High Strangeness
episodes.overview: An otherworldly encounter puts Tree Trunks on the trail of a conspiracy in the Candy Kingdom.

episodes.name: Horse and Ball
episodes.overview: When disaster befalls James Baxter, it’s up to Finn and Jake to help him pick up the pieces.

episodes.name: Jelly Beans Have Power
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum's scientific mind must wrestle with her Elemental magic potential when she's faced with a Crystal Entity.

episodes.name: Islands Part 1: The Invitation
episodes.overview: A mysterious craft invades Ooo and Finn believes it may hold the secrets to his past.

episodes.name: Islands Part 2: Whipple the Happy Dragon
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, and Susan set sail on a ocean voyage full of wonders and danger.

episodes.name: Islands Part 3: Mysterious Island
episodes.overview: After waking up alone and shipwrecked, Finn investigates a bizarre island in search of his friends.

episodes.name: Islands Part 4: Imaginary Resources
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake travel to a land where reality has been redesigned and improved.

episodes.name: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
episodes.overview: While exploring some futuristic ruins, Susan sees glimpses of a familiar girl.

episodes.name: Islands Part 6: Min & Marty
episodes.overview: An unexpected revelation from Susan leads Finn closer to answers about his past.

episodes.name: Islands Part 7: Helpers
episodes.overview: Finn and his friends journey to a last refuge called Founders Island.

episodes.name: Islands Part 8: The Light Cloud
episodes.overview: Finn confronts the power behind Founders Island, but will he ever return home to Ooo?

episodes.name: Orb
episodes.overview: During the journey home from their sea-faring adventure; Finn, Jake, and BMO encounter a mysterious force that enters their dreams.

episodes.name: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, and BMO return from their voyage to a radically changed Ooo.

episodes.name: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
episodes.overview: The friends learn the story of what happened to Ooo, while Betty continues her attempt to reach Simon, but she's interrupted by someone out to steal her magic.

episodes.name: Elements Part 3: Winter Light
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and Ice King break into the Ice World to confront the power-hungry evildoer responsible for the chaos in Ooo and try to rescue Betty.

episodes.name: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
episodes.overview: After taking a nap, Finn and Jake get separated from Betty and the Ice King. They need to get back and Jake needs to go pee.

episodes.name: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
episodes.overview: In order to save Ooo, Finn and Jake must gather the four elemental gems. They go to the Slime Kingdom and have to gather Slime Princess's gem.

episodes.name: Elements Part 6: Happy Warrior
episodes.overview: After gathering the Slime jewel, Finn and LSP go to the Fire Kingdom, to gather the Flame Jewel. Everything has turned even hotter than before.

episodes.name: Elements Part 7: Hero Heart
episodes.overview: After going to the Fire Kingdom, Finn becomes taken over by fire. LSP has to save him before he destroys the candy kingdom.

episodes.name: Elements Part 8: Skyhooks II
episodes.overview: After saving Finn the human during a battle between the candy kingdom and the fire kingdom it is discovered that LSP is made of anti-elemental magic and restores Ooo to it's former state.

episodes.name: Abstract
episodes.overview: Jake struggles through the personal changes happening to him as a mysterious encounter in a dream with his brother Jermaine begins to haunt him.

episodes.name: Ketchup
episodes.overview: BMO and Marceline play catch up on recent events.

episodes.name: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
episodes.overview: While performing a reading of 'Fiona and Cake', Ice King is confronted by a familiar figure.

episodes.name: Whispers
episodes.overview: While safeguarding a frightened Sweet P, Finn is led into a confrontation with an old foe.

episodes.name: Three Buckets
episodes.overview: Finn and Fern's carefree visit to some old ruins turns disastrous.

episodes.name: The Wild Hunt
episodes.overview: A fierce creature is terrorizing the Candy Kingdom but before Finn can slay the beast, he must first overcome a guilty conscience.

episodes.name: Always BMO Closing
episodes.overview: BMO and Ice King hit the road as door to door salesmen and stumble upon an irresistible opportunity.

episodes.name: Son of Rap Bear
episodes.overview: When Flame Princess is coaxed into a high stakes battle against the indomitable Son of Rap Bear, Finn must help her search for a new strategy.

episodes.name: Bonnibel Bubblegum
episodes.overview: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to harken back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

episodes.name: Seventeen
episodes.overview: A mysterious knight crashes Finn's birthday bash and presents him with a dangerous gift.

episodes.name: Ring of Fire
episodes.overview: When an old flame comes calling on urgent business, Tree Trunks reconsiders both her wild past and her tranquil present.

episodes.name: Marcy & Hunson
episodes.overview: After helping with the creation of a new sword, Hunson Abadeer comes back to try and regain his daughter's love.

episodes.name: The First Investigation
episodes.overview: Kim Kil Whan tasks Jake and Finn to investigate reports of a haunting in one of Kim Kil Whan's properties "Joshua and Margaret Investigations" since something in there traumatized his top employee Renny Hamlond and does not pay any rent for inhabiting the place.

episodes.name: Blenanas
episodes.overview: Finn's latest literary work meets with only derision, so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

episodes.name: Jake the Starchild
episodes.overview: In order to fulfill his grand destiny, Jake is spirited away by a strangely familiar shape-shifting alien.

episodes.name: Temple of Mars
episodes.overview: Searching for answers on Mars, Finn and Jermaine discover that they must first survive a cunning Martian mental trap.

episodes.name: Gumbaldia
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake, as ambassadors of the Candy Kingdom, travel to a powerful new city-state in a last ditch effort to stave off war.

episodes.name: Come Along With Me
episodes.overview: In the distant future, many years after the outcome of the Gum War, two friends named Beth and Shermy recover a rusty old mechanical arm that once belonged to Finn after it is dropped by a Prize Ball Guardian.

10.name: Season 10
10.overview: The tenth and final season of Adventure Time.
